This paper is about search-based software testing, which is a subfield of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper proposes a random walk based algorithm for test case generation, which involves optimizing a problem, making it relevant to programming languages (cs.PL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The algorithm also involves sorting test goals to improve search efficiency, which could be related to machine learning (cs.LG) and control systems (cs.SY).
